A Study on Application of Big Data of Railway Freight Marketing at China Railway Nanning Group
CHEN Xiaohui, YANG Li
(Freight Department, China Railway Nanning Group Co. Ltd., Nanning 530029, Guangxi, China)
Abstract: To promote application of information technologies in railway freight marketing strategies and build a new freight marketing model based on big data, this paper studies the railway freight marketing data from the aspects of strengthening market research, analysis and prediction, improving customer relationship management, developing modern railway logistics, optimizing allocation of transportation resources and upgrading freight revenue management. Based on an overview of application analysis of freight marketing data of China Railway Nanning Group, to provide reference for constructing a new freight marketing model based on big data, this paper puts forward the following strategies: establishing a freight big data application platform, optimizing and integrating social resources, improving internal transport organization, promoting cultivating versatile talents, upgrading the freight marketing mechanism and offering customized services. Keywords: Big Data; Railway Transport; Freight Marketing; Decision Support System; Improvement Strategies

